ROOT CAUSE: `src/be_vm.c:745` (inside `opcase(FLIP)`) implements Berry's unary bitwise-not operator using arithmetic negation: `var_setint(dst, -a->v.i);`. That is the same numeric operation as unary minus, not bitwise complement. For an integer value 11, arithmetic negation produces -11, but bitwise flip should produce `~11 == -12`, so `tests/bitwise.be` fails on the first `~` assertion.

